\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. orientalis} Miller, {\i Gard. Dict.} ed. 8, no. 3 (1768) ({\i C. duinensis} Scop.). Shrub or small tree. Leaves 2·5-6 cm, ovate or elliptical, acute, biserrate, cuneate to rounded at base, sparsely pubescent on the veins beneath. Infructescence 3-5 cm; involucre c. 2 cm, triangular-ovate, serrate but not lobed.{\i  S.E. Europe, extending westwards to Sicilia}. Al Bu Gr Hu It Ju Rm Rs(K) Si Tu.
