\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. avellana} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 998 (1753). Shrub up to 6 m, with smooth, brown bark. Leaves suborbicular, acuminate, biserrate, often shallowly lobed, cordate at base; stipules oblong, obtuse. Catkins up to 8 cm, pendent. Infructescence of 1-4 nuts; involucre about as large as the nut, divided to half-way or a little more, into more or less ovate, usually irregularly dentate or laciniate lobes about as long as the nut; nut 1·5-2 cm, brown, with a hard, woody shell. 2n = 22.{\i  Europe, except some islands and the extreme north and north-east}. All except Bl Fa Is Sb; doubtfully native in Cr. naturalized in Az.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. colurna} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 999 (1753). Like {\b 1} but usually a tree, up to 20 m; stipules lanceolate, acuminate; catkins up to 12 cm; involucre much longer than the nut, divided almost to base into many long-acuminate, serrate lobes.{\i  Balkan peninsula S.W. Romania.} Al Bu Gr Ju Rm Tu.
\par

